
	**********************************************************************************
	Differences from code in article Linux/Documentation/target/tcmu-design.txt
	**********************************************************************************

	- All code in one file

	- We need to include some libraries to make it work:

		#include <fcntl.h>                      - for codes O_RDONLY and etc
		#include <stdlib.h>			- for stroull
		#include <stdio.h>			- for io
		#include <unistd.h>			- for open, read, etc
		#include <string.h>			- for strncmp
		#include <stdbool.h>			- for bool
		#include <sys/mman.h>			- for mmap
		#include <linux/target_core_user.h>	- trivial

	- Need to define codes for SCSI (such as NO_SENSE)

	- Some variable declarations lost in article
		i.e.: unsigned int ret

	- We must check file-opening error
		i.e.: if (fd == -1)

	- Type cast (__u32) added for tcmu_hdr_get_len function call

	**********************************************************************************
	Compilation and execution
	**********************************************************************************

	Compiled with gcc and clang in terminal
	Compiled with JetBrains Clion

	Compilation: gcc -o tcmu_example -c tcmu_example.c

	Problem with execution:
		We'll get exit code 1, because we don't have .../uio0/name file

	Ideas about solution:
		It's UIO feature. This code is only manager, that works in endless loop and
		processes operations.
		To make it work we must have userspace driver with its own device
		We must register this device with call such as uio_register_device(...)
		Link: https://lwn.net/Articles/232575/

	**********************************************************************************
	Plans
	**********************************************************************************

	Read more about uio. Create our own device and driver code.
	Make it work with existing tcmu_example code.

